Date: Wed, 23 Mar 2011 13:08:09 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 3/7] WRHV: MIPS: Only boot core setup max ASID

Since max ASID is global limitation for all of cores, so only
permit boot core to get max ASID via VBI call.

Signed-off-by: Yang Shi <yang.shi@windriver.com>
---
 arch/mips/kernel/vbi/wrhv.c |    3 ++-
 1 files changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/arch/mips/kernel/vbi/wrhv.c b/arch/mips/kernel/vbi/wrhv.c
index dc7ec7f..699862f 100644
--- a/arch/mips/kernel/vbi/wrhv.c
+++ b/arch/mips/kernel/vbi/wrhv.c
@@ -121,7 +121,8 @@ void __cpuinit wrhv_per_cpu_trap_init(void)
 	wr_vb_control->vb_control_regs.asid = init_cfg.asid;
 	wr_vb_control->vb_control_regs.vmmu_handle = init_cfg.vmmu_handle;
 
-	get_max_asid();
+	if (cpu == 0)
+		get_max_asid();
 
 	TLBMISS_HANDLER_SETUP();
 }
